case 2 units. So 1 unit left and 2 units up. This gives us our first point at

00:02:23.114 --> 00:02:28.940
negative 1, 2. Then we can move 1 unit right. And 2 units up to give ourselves

00:02:28.940 --> 00:02:35.687
another at 1, 2 and here is a 3rd parabola y equals 3x squared. Notice that the

00:02:35.687 --> 00:02:41.008
turning point of the vertex where this parabola is still at 0,0, the origin. To

00:02:41.008 --> 00:02:45.450
find other points on this purple parabola we're going to use our a value. We

00:02:45.450 --> 00:02:54.900
can move 1 unit left and 3 units up. This gives us coordinate of negative 1, 3.

00:02:54.900 --> 00:02:59.052
To find another point on the graph, we'll go the opposite way. We'll go 1 unit

00:02:59.052 --> 00:03:05.218
right, and this time 3 units up. This gives us a point of 1 comma 3. The a

00:03:05.218 --> 00:03:10.120
value is always a quick way to get 1 point that is to the left of the vertex.

00:03:10.120 --> 00:03:13.585
And 1 point that is to the right of the vertex whenever parabola is in the form

